<!-- question6 start---------------------->
<TABLE BORDER="1" WIDTH="97%" BGCOLOR="#0099FF" BORDERCOLOR="#0099FF" CELLPADDING="0">
<TR> 
                  <TD BGCOLOR="#0099FF" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="162"><IMG SRC="../chao_images/snap/snap_dx04.gif" WIDTH="160" HEIGHT="120"></TD>
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="328"> 
<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=3>
<TR> 
<TD BGCOLOR="RED" VALIGN="center" HEIGHT=16 COLSPAN=3><IMG SRC="../chao_images/q.gif"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF"> 
<B>Is it true that Chao become adults?</B></FONT></TD>
<TR> 
<TD BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" VALIGN="CENTER" COLSPAN=3><A NAME="6"><FONT SIZE="2">
Is it true that Chao become adults?<BR>
What will change when they become adults?</FONT></A></TD>
</TABLE>
<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=3>
<TR> 
<TD VALIGN="bottom" HEIGHT=16 COLSPAN=3 BGCOLOR="#FFCC00"><IMG SRC="../chao_images/a.gif"></TD>
<TR> 
                        <TD BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" VALIGN="CENTER" COLSPAN=3><FONT SIZE=2> Yes, that's true. 
                          Chao who were born from an egg will eventually become 
                          adults. Their body size doesn't change much, though.</FONT> 
                          <P> <FONT SIZE=2> Chao also have a life span and will 
                            die when their time comes. Every creature dies eventually, 
                            and it's very sad to say good-bye. If you become a 
                            very good friend of your Chao, Chao will remember 
                            you and will be reborn from an egg after they die. 
                            This is called reincarnation. Chao is a truly mysterious 
                            creature. You can see the chart of the Chao's life 
                            cycle below. This may give you more information about 
                            a Chao's life when you raise them. </FONT><img src="../chao_images/chao_lifecycle_en.gif" width="300"> 
                        </TD>
<TR> 
<TD WIDTH=34% VALIGN="top"> 
<FONT SIZE="2">&#134;<BR>
When the color of the Chao's cocoon turns light blue, that Chao will become an adult.<BR>
The different types of Chao, such as Dark Chao, Hero Chao, and Neutral Chao, are decided here.
 Your Chao's ability, such as swimming, flying, running, power and normal, are also decided at this point.</FONT>  
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=32% VALIGN="top"> 
<FONT SIZE="2">&#134;<BR>
Your Chao can become five different types and develop their abilities, such as swimming type, flying type, running type, powerful type and normal type.</FONT> 
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=34%>
<FONT SIZE="2">&#134;<BR>
When the time comes, your Chao will die. 
If your Chao is not treated well, it becomes a gray cocoon and disappears. 
If your Chao is treated well, it becomes a pink cocoon and come back to life again as an egg.<BR>
If you want to leave a good impression with your Chao, try being a good friend to your Chao!</FONT></TD>
</TABLE>
</TD></TABLE>
